The analysis and prediction This analysis tries to understand the relationship between different factors and their influence on medical charges. Machine learning models are then developed to predic charges based on the expaliner facorts in the data

In [308]:
#Creating a function for age group
def age_group(age):
    #Defining Age groups
    if (age>=18 and age<=35):
        return "youth"
    if (age>=36 and age<=50):
        return "mid_age"
    else:
        return "senior_age"
data["age_group"]=data["age"].apply(age_group)

Data Processing 2¶

Handling Outliers¶

In [319]:
#replacing outliers with median in age using IQR
for i in data["age"]:
    q1=data["age"].quantile(0.25)
    q3=data["age"].quantile(0.75)
    iqr=q3-q1
    lower=q1-1.5*iqr
    upper=q3+1.5*iqr
    if i>upper or i<lower:
        data2["age"]=data["age"].replace(i,np.median(data["age"]))
figure =figsize=(8,3)
plt.title("age after Outlier Replacement")
sns.boxplot(data["age"],color="g")
plt.show()
In [41]:
for i in data["bmi"]:
    q1=data["bmi"].quantile(0.25)
    q3=data["bmi"].quantile(0.75)
    iqr=q3-q1
    lower=q1-1.5*iqr
    upper=q3+1.5*iqr
    if i>upper or i<lower:
        data["bmi"]=data["bmi"].replace(i,np.median(data["bmi"]))
figure=figsize=(8,4)
plt.title("bmi after outlier imputation")
sns.boxplot(data["bmi"],color="r")
plt.show()

In [43]:
from sklearn import preprocessing
for col in data.select_dtypes(include=["object"]).columns:
    le=preprocessing.LabelEncoder()
    le.fit(data[col].unique())
    data[col]=le.transform(data[col])
